1. Open an app in Kissflow.
2. Go to Application builder.
3. On the left navigation bar, go to Variables.
4. Click Global variable and enter the details of the variable.

- Variable name: The key name for your variable.
- Description: The description for your variable.
- Variable type: You can select the following data types: Text, Number, DateTime, Boolean, Object, Array of objects, Array of strings.

- Default value: Specify the default value for the key. The default value differs based on the data type.

Click Create to save the variable.

Alternatively, you can also add new global variables from the JavaScript editor within a form.

Sample javascript for declaring global and local variables

```javascript

let idResp await kf.api("/id");

let accountId idResp._accId;

let pageId=idResp._pageId;

//global variable

kf.app.setVariable("Account_Id", accountId);

//local variable

kf.app.page.setVariable("Page_Id", pageId);

let resp await kf.api(form/2/$&#123;accountId&#125;/Asset_Master/
$&#123;pageId&#125;/Systems_one/view/list?apply_preference=true&_application_id=IT_Asset_Management_System');

await kf.app.setVariable("Asset_Master_Count", resp.count \|\| 0);

let list_resp await kf.api(`/form/2/$&#123;accountId&#125;/Asset_Entry/

$&#123;pageId&#125;/view/All_Entries/list?page_number=1&page_size=100&_application_id=IT_Asset_Management_System', &#123; "method": "POST" &#125;);
```


On the Variables page, all existing global variables will be listed along with their name, description, data type, and default value. You can also update or delete global variables from this section.

Homepage overview

Your homepage is your starting point after signing in to Kissflow. It gives you an at-a-glance summary of your items, your workflows, and other key information, so you can pick up where you left off without digging through menus.

