Matrix is like kanban with a secondary categorization through rows. You plot items on a grid, choosing fields for both the horizontal and vertical pivots. This layout is best suited for slicing and dicing board data, and for resource balancing and reallocation.

You can group rows and columns by status, assignee, or custom user fields. Items that don't fit any group are pooled under Uncategorized.

{/* TODO: verify screenshot matches current product UI */}

The status log captures every status change for an item, along with the time spent in each status. Open an item, click the Item log tab in the right navigation strip, and select the Status log subtab.

{/* TODO: verify screenshot matches current product UI */}

Use the time spent in each status to spot items that are stuck — especially critical ones — so they get resolved without delays.

Open an item from any layout and make your changes in the Details tab on the right. All changes are saved automatically.

- Change status — select the new status from the Status dropdown. You can also mark an item as completed by clicking the check mark on its card, which moves it to the board's completed status.

{/* TODO: verify screenshot matches current product UI */}

